The "manager" on duty was rude and impolite when I asked to use the restroom as a paying customer. He said that it was not in service and there was nothing he could do. When I tried to have him address my concerns I was met with an eye roll. I asked for a corporate number and was told that one was not available to give me. I asked the cashier for the "managers" name, and he said "he didn't know his name." I asked the cashier to page the manger for me, and when the manger appeared, his attitude was worse. I asked for his name to make a complaint, to which he replied "take a picture of my name tag" and i was met with more attitude when i said that the tag was illegible. I asked him to spell it for me, and he said "he does not care, that i should do whatever I want." This is completely unacceptable, and the worse experience I have encountered as a loyal Popeye's customer for years.

I ordered spicy chicken and they said they were out of spicy chicken and tried to convince me to take the mild chicken. I told them I wanted spicy and they said the spicy would take 15 mins to cook so I decided to wait. Five minutes later they told me the spicy chicken was ready but when I tasted the chicken it was not spicy at all. When I brought this to the attention of the cashier she told me that it was indeed spicy and that is how their spicy tastes. I know the chicken was not spicy because they told me it would take 15 mins but my order was ready in 5 mins or less. I did not like being lied to and I did not enjoy the mild chicken they gave me.
